@startuml
title Sequence Diagram for AddItemCommand (Parse Routing and Dispatch)

autonumber
hide footbox

actor User
participant ":UI" as UI
participant ":InventoryDock" as InventoryDock
participant ":Parser" as Parser
participant ":AddCommandParser" as AddCommandParser
participant ":AddItemCommandParser" as AddItemCommandParser

note right of AddCommandParser
This diagram uses the fruits workflow
as a representative example.
The same routing pattern applies
to other supported categories.
end note

User -> UI: enter add command
activate UI
UI -> InventoryDock: input
activate InventoryDock
InventoryDock -> Parser: parse(input)
activate Parser

Parser -> AddCommandParser: parse(arguments)
activate AddCommandParser
AddCommandParser -> AddCommandParser: validateRequiredFields(trimmedInput)
activate AddCommandParser
AddCommandParser --> AddCommandParser
deactivate AddCommandParser

AddCommandParser -> AddCommandParser: extractCategory(trimmedInput)
activate AddCommandParser
AddCommandParser --> AddCommandParser: category
deactivate AddCommandParser

alt category == fruits
    AddCommandParser -> AddItemCommandParser: handleFruit(trimmedInput)
    activate AddItemCommandParser
    AddItemCommandParser --> AddCommandParser: command
    deactivate AddItemCommandParser
else other supported category
    AddCommandParser -> AddItemCommandParser: handleCategory(input)
    activate AddItemCommandParser
    AddItemCommandParser --> AddCommandParser: command
    deactivate AddItemCommandParser
else else
    AddCommandParser --> Parser: throw InvalidCommandException("Unknown category: " + category)
end

AddCommandParser --> Parser: command
deactivate AddCommandParser
Parser --> InventoryDock: command
deactivate Parser
deactivate InventoryDock
deactivate UI
@enduml


